      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "There was plenty of merit in the latest performance of GLAMOUR FOX (1) when she came from a very wide barrier and finished third, beaten 4 metres, in a nice return to form at Wagga. Much better served by the ace draw so should get her chance. DIDNT I (8) worked but was too good first up and didn't do a bad job when fourth from a wide barrier at Wagga last time out. Race fit now and she is a player if things go her way from the back line. NIFTY AMBITION (6) has produced some decent recent efforts at Wagga, finishing midfield from this barrier last time and second from the back row three back. Contender. GIRL JUST FLY (4) was down the track last time but came from this barrier to score at Wagga prior. Could bounce back.",
